{{Quote|Watch this--Little trick I picked up flying dragon kites on Coruscant... put 'em on spin dry... and turbulence does the rest!|Wes Janson|<ref name="X-Wing Rogue Squadron 1">[[X-Wing Rogue Squadron 1|''X-Wing Rogue Squadron'' 1]]</ref>}}
The '''dragon kite maneuver''' was a [[Starfighter combat/Legends|starfighter combat]] technique that was invented by [[Wes Janson/Legends|Wes Janson]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], while in combat with [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE/LN starfighters]] over [[Cilpar]] in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]]. The tactic was only effective while flying in an [[Atmosphere/Legends|atmosphere]]; it consisted of deliberately spinning one's [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] in order to create a pocket of turbulence to form in the craft's wake, which would ideally make any pursuing enemy ships buffet in the unstable air. In the instance that Wes first attempted the maneuver it worked, causing the two TIEs chasing him to crash into one another. Unfortunately for Janson, the debris resulting from the collision also downed his [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]].

==Behind the scenes==
The tactic is not given an official name, but it is referred to as being similar to a technique used in combat kite-flying competitions.

